cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for crowd counting and detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of a multi-column architecture and feedback processing, which are common techniques in deep learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also presents a novel training regime, which could fall under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with the challenges of detecting people in dense crowds, which could fall under the categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.RO (Robotics).
